A '''system''' is a set of [[entities]]{{dn|date=October 2019}}, real or abstract, comprising a whole where each component interacts with or is related to at least one other component and they all serve a common objective. For the purpose of organizing articles into categories, there are four major type of system which can reasonably be expected to contain every type of system under its category tree: '''[[:Category:Physical systems|Physical systems]]''', '''[[:Category:Biological systems|Biological systems]]''', '''[[:Category:Social systems|Social systems]]''', and '''[[:Category:Conceptual systems|Conceptual systems]]'''.

