[[Category:Corporate groups]]
[[Category:Structure]]
[[Category:Entities]]
[[Category:Main topic classifications]]
[[Category:Society]]

A '''corporate group''' is two or more [[individual]]s, usually in the form of a [[family]], [[clan]], [[organization]], or [[company]]. A major distinction between different [[political culture]]s is whether they believe the [[individual]] is the basic unit of their society, in which case they are [[Individualism|individualistic]], or whether corporate groups are the basic unit of their society, in which case they are [[corporatism|corporatist]].
